<TITLE> 350 receive Best Taxpayer Award 2009 </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sep 15 (bdnews24.com)The National Board of Revenue on Tuesday presented 350 people with its Best Taxpayer Award for 2009. Finance minister AMA Muhith presented crests and certificates to the award winners to mark National Income Tax Day 2009, at a ceremony at the Bangabandhu International Conference Centre. Two individuals from each city corporation were recognised for paying their taxes for the longest period of time and three for paying the highest amount of tax, while the same numbers of recipients were recognised for their efforts in each of the 64 districts. In Dhaka City Corporation, Syed Mahbub and ASM Mahmood received the Best Taxpayer Award for paying their income taxes for the longest time, while Anwar Hossain, Kaus Miah and Iqbal Haider Choudhury paid the most income tax in the FY 2008-09. bd
